In this article, President Donald Trump discusses the positive impact of the tax cuts and tax reform implemented by his administration. He highlights that starting next year, Americans will be able to complete their taxes on a simple, single sheet of paper. The tax law includes a doubled standard deduction and child tax credit, as well as lowered rates for hardworking families. Trump also mentions the benefits that Americans have already seen, such as bigger paychecks and lower utility bills. He emphasizes the creation of jobs and investments by companies, including Apple and Fiat Chrysler. The article also mentions the repeal of Obamacare's individual mandate and the opening up of the Arctic National Wildlife Refuge for energy exploration. Trump concludes by expressing his desire for all Americans to have good jobs and opportunities, and states that America is strong and winning.